   2024},
Year = {2024},
Pages = {232-239},
Note = {8th International Conference on Digital Technology in Education, Berlin,
   GERMANY, AUG 07-09, 2024},
Abstract = {This study aimed to investigate the perspectives of instructors on the
   impact of ChatGPT as a teaching and learning tool. The research followed
   a mixed method approach which included a survey and a focus group
   discussion. A total 18 instructors affiliated with the Military
   Technological College in Muscat, Oman, responded to the survey.
   Additionally, 5 instructors joined a focus group discussion to share
   their views on the integration of ChatGPT in engineering education. The
   survey was analyzed using descriptive analysis while the data of the
   focus group discussion was analyzed using thematic analysis. The
   findings showed that instructors have a very high perception of the use
   of ChatGPT in engineering education. The results also showed the
   importance of having well-defined and widely communicated guidelines for
   using ChatGPT in engineering education. The findings also showed that
   instructors need to promote ethical awareness, have training on AI
   tools, and take assessment redesign into consideration.},
