Pages = {3572-3581},
Month = {NOV},
Abstract = {The article highlights the results of a survey of students at Ukrainian
   universities on the use of artificial intelligence (AI) systems in the
   educational process. The main advantages and risks of using generative
   AI in education have been analyzed. For collecting data, a questionnaire
   created with Google Forms was used. There were 177 students from
   different regions of Ukraine who participated in the survey. It has been
   found that the vast majority of respondents (94.4\%) use AI to perform
   various educational tasks. The most common AI services among students
   turned out to be ChatGPT, Gemini, MidJourney and DALL-E. It has been
   found that Ukrainian teachers allow the use of ChatGPT in classes with
   certain restrictions and instructions. 90.4\% of students adhere to the
   principles of academic integrity and process the text generated by
   ChatGPT.Further research is planned to determine the possibilities of
   ChatGPT for developing critical thinking through reading and writing.},
