   Systems-NiDS, Athens, GREECE, SEP 24-26, 2025},
Organization = {University of West Attica; Athens University of Economics \& Business;
   Greek Computer Society},
Abstract = {The influence of ChatGPT in introductory programming courses has
   received increasing attention in recent years. However, most research
   concentrates on programming courses in developed countries and
   universities, leaving a gap in understanding the effect of ChatGPT on
   K-12 students. To contribute to this field, this study examines the
   impact of ChatGPT-assisted learning on students' performance, learning
   experience, and attitudes in an introductory programming course in the
   Philippines. We conducted a between-subjects experiment involving 40
   ninth-grade students divided into Manual and ChatGPT groups. We compared
   their performance by analyzing their assessment scores. Moreover, we
   conducted a survey to understand students' learning experiences and
   attitudes during the course. Results show that ChatGPT does not
   significantly affect students' performance, emphasizing the importance
   of strategic implementation and the development of students' AI
   literacy. Nonetheless, the ChatGPT group demonstrated positive learning
   experiences and attitudes. This outcome shows the potential of ChatGPT
   to enhance students' learning experience.},
