Pages = {1014-1023},
Month = {MAY},
Abstract = {The widespread penetration of Artificial Intelligence (AI) tools has
   created many chances for educators. AI applications can be used to
   prepare lectures and classroom exercises - from creating lesson plans,
   presentations, and lectures, generating tasks for practical work and
   self-assessment to generating exam tasks and quiz questions. This study
   presents the generation of quiz questions and tasks by ChatGPT on the
   topic of number systems. Findings show that the generation of quiz
   questions and their answers, practical tasks, and their solutions has
   taken ChatGPT minutes, less than teacher's time preparing a quiz. In the
   current research, ChatGPT has demonstrated its capabilities to generate
   different types of questions relevant to the learning content, clearly
   and correctly defined, as well as practical tasks. The presence of
   inaccuracies indicates that generative models are still developing. The
   research outcomes have shown that teachers must integrate ChatGPT into
   their activities responsibly, considering the possible challenges and
   threats.},
