Note = {2024 World Engineering Education Forum - Global Engineering Deans
   Council, Sydney, AUSTRALIA, DEC 02-05, 2024},
Abstract = {This study examines ChatGPT, an Artificial Intelligence (AI) tool, to
   enhance learning and assessment in educational settings. The core of the
   research is the ``Microbe Detectives{''} activity, where students use
   biochemical tests to identify microorganisms and then use ChatGPT to
   validate their findings. This approach is designed to improve students'
   laboratory skills and promote the ethical and responsible use of AI. The
   study includes a survey to evaluate the usability, cost, response
   quality, and overall student satisfaction with ChatGPT. The results
   indicate that although only 25\% of students accurately identified the
   microorganism using only biochemical tests, the majority found ChatGPT
   helpful in exploring different outcomes and strengthening their
   conclusions. While some students expressed dissatisfaction with the
   accuracy of ChatGPT's responses, most appreciated the integration of AI
   into their learning activities. The study emphasises the importance of
   developing AI systems prioritising fairness, transparency, and
   accountability to build trust in their educational application. It also
   highlights the need for comprehensive training for educators and
   students to ensure the responsible and effective use of AI tools.},
